 seeds","2 tsp cumin seeds","1 tbsp coriander seeds","1 tsp ground turmeric","20 fresh curry leaves","1 tbsp brown mustard seeds","2 tsp dried chilli flakes","1 tsp salt flakes","½ tsp black peppercorns"]},{"title":"Bread rolls","content":["280 g water","1 tsp dried yeast","½ tsp salt flakes","500 g baker's flour","30 g olive oil, plus extra for brushing"]}],"id":"r119902","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-4LB8OT2VNVg\/XZau0LtWl6I\/AAAAAAAAhnM\/taRoFZT64YI7pg1cQBOyvHGvE2FLrQIlACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1r3vmSo-m_vgkDHw.png","title":"Vadouvan spiced mini rolls","publishedAt":"2017-01-22T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.4 g","fat":"4.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.4 g","calories":"577 kJ \/ 137 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, kitchen towel, silicone bread mat, large bowl, baking tray (20 x 30 cm), pastry brush, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Double or triple onion quantities to make enough for burger and hot dog toppings.","Remaining Vadouvan spice mix can be stored in a sealable jar in a cool, dry place. Use it as a curry spice base, or add to soups, butter, marinades and dressings.","Serve these rolls with the Yoghurt soup cups (refer to the recipe on this recipe chip).","Make larger rolls for sit-down dinner parties."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","2h 30m","20 portions"]}